snippet: The second of five programs in the Fall for Dance festival at City Center featured Pam Tanowitz’s “Fortune,” Twyla Tharp’s “Sinatra Suite,” Martha Graham’s “Chronicle” and Peter Quanz’s “Luminous.”
abstract: Alastair Macaulay reviews second of five programs at the Fall for Dance Festival at City Center, featuring performances by Juilliard's dance students.
lead_paragraph: The second of five programs in the Fall for Dance festival at City Center featured Pam Tanowitz’s “Fortune,” Twyla Tharp’s “Sinatra Suite,” Martha Graham’s “Chronicle” and Peter Quanz’s “Luminous.”
